        <h3>What Is This?</h3>
        <p>
            This is a free web app designed for astronomers, star-gazers, and anyone interested in deep-space observations.
            You will be able to locate anything&sup1; ranging from star clusters to nebulae to galaxies from a collection of over 200 deep-space objects.
            This app includes astronomical objects from the Messier Catalog and the Caldwell Catalog, compiled by French astronomer Charles Messier and
            English astronomer Patrick Moore, respectively.
            Take a look at the <a class="link" href="/Search">Search</a> page to learn more about the various objects, such as their type, 
            visibility, and best viewing conditions.
            <br />
            <div class="footnote row">
                <span class="col-1">&sup1;</span>
                <span class="col-11">
                    Please note that some objects are only visible during certain seasons, and some objects may never be seen from 
                    your location due to Earth's rotation about the sky.
                </span>
            </div>
        </p>
