        <h3>How Does Tracking Work?</h3>
        <p>
            You can track the location of any deep-sky object across time from a collection of over 200 objects, from anywhere around the world, with accurate results.
            Upon choosing an object, you have a choice of tracking over a span of seconds, minutes, hours, days, weeks, months, and years.
            The results will display the location of the object in the sky for each interval of the track (i.e., at hour 1, hour 2, hour 3, and so on).
            This is perfect if you need to know where the object is ahead of time, or if you want to visualize the object's path relative to Earth's rotation.
            In addition, you can also find out when and where an object will be at its highest point in your night-sky for better viewing.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article class="about-article">
        @*<div class="about-img-content">
